===Etymology===
:Old English ''thanc'' (thought, gratitude) of Germanic origin

===Noun===

# (Usually plural) An expression of appreciation (for instance, used in phrases such as ''to give thanks'', ''to owe thanks'', ''to receive thanks'').
# (In plural: almost as an interjection, but still able to take a qualifying adjective) Thank you (''thanks'', ''many thanks'', ''thanks a lot'').

